article.headline: Pacific 64, Cal St.-Fullerton 55
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. -- Travis Fulton scored 19 points Thursday night to lead Pacific to a 64-55 victory over Cal State-Fullerton. Colin Beatty added 11 points for the Tigers (16-12, 10-5 Big West), who held the Titans to 16 first-half points and stopped a two-game losing streak. Kwame Vaughn had 16 points, seven rebounds and five assists for Fullerton (14-14, 6-9). Alex Harris chipped in 12 points. The Titans came as close as five points with 3 minutes to play, but Pacific scored eight of the next 10 points to put the game out of reach.
